{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["Preheat oven to 170°C. Set aside a baking tray (30 x 40 cm).","Place butter, flour and salt into mixing bowl and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 6<b>, or until mixture resembles breadcrumbs.","Add egg yolk and water and blend <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer onto a clean work surface, shape into a ball and wrap in plastic wrap. Place into refrigerator for 15 minutes. Do not clean mixing bowl.","Transfer dough onto a lightly floured piece of baking paper (30 x 40 cm) and roll dough into a circle (30 cm diameter). Transfer pastry with baking paper onto baking tray and set aside."]},{"title":"Filling","content":["Place cheese into mixing bowl and grate <b>5 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place butter and white portion of the spring onions\/shallots into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add all remaining filling ingredients, except milk, including reserved cheese and combine <b>5 sec\/\/speed 3<b>.","Spread mixture onto pastry, leaving a 5 cm border on all sides. Fold over pastry border, pleating pastry as you fold to create a crust.  Brush top of pastry with milk and bake for 25-30 minutes (170°C), or until pastry is puffed and golden. Meanwhile, make creamy tofu dressing while galette bakes. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Creamy tofu dressing","content":["Place a jug onto mixing bowl lid and weigh oil into it. Set aside.","Place garlic into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add all remaining dressing ingredients, except oil, and mix <b>3 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Mix <b>2 min\/speed 4<b>, slowly pouring oil onto mixing bowl lid letting it trickle into mixing bowl.","Allow to cool for 5-10 minutes before serving with galette."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pastry","content":["70 g unsalted butter, chilled and cut into pieces (3-4 cm)","120 g self-raising flour, plus extra for dusting","2 pinches sea salt","1 egg yolk","30 g chilled water"]},{"title":"Filling","content":["200 g cheddar cheese, cut into pieces (3 cm)","40 g unsalted butter","140 g spring onion\/shallot, trimmed, white portion cut into halves and green portion cut into thin slices","100 g flaked almonds","1 tbsp wholegrain mustard","2 egg yolks","1 egg","1 tsp dried marjoram","2 tbsp full cream milk"]},{"title":"Creamy tofu dressing","content":["200 g extra virgin olive oil","3 garlic cloves","150 g silken tofu","1 tbsp seeded mustard","60 g balsamic vinegar","2 tbsp miso paste"]}],"id":"r101747","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-reMVxyLpijU\/XZVRzO3ygCI\/AAAAAAAAdTI\/_XdxWhwHG2gkT5SUUDEjNqTn91Gr4GKwgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_yQv83xP65Ct9APXV.png","title":"Cheese and spring onion galette","publishedAt":"2016-07-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"18.5 g","fat":"70.1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"20.8 g","calories":"3305 kJ \/ 786 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray (30 x 40 cm), plastic wrap, rolling pin, baking paper, bowl, pastry brush, jug, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Store leftover dressing in the refrigerator and use on green salads, potato or pasta salads or steamed greens.","Try turning this galette into a lovely hors-d'oeuvre by making them into individual tartlets.","This recipe provides a range of nutrients including vitamin B12, zinc, calcium and protein."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 15m","6 portions"]}